I’ve worked with my colleagues on the Approps committee to improve the readiness & operational efficiency of active duty and reserve bases in our state. I believe these MS projects will fare well as the Senate & House work toward a single bill that can be signed into law. Read:

Adoption is a beautiful blessing, providing children with a stable home & loving family, and providing a family with the joy that is a child. November is #NationalAdoptionMonth, a time not only to celebrate adoption, but to raise awareness about what an excellent option it is.

The Senate produced a strong, bipartisan Ag Approps Bill that supports our state's role in improving ag production/innovation. The demands for infrastructure in many rural communities are acute, so I appreciate the resources provided in our bill to address water systems & health.

The border crisis is no secret, but Biden’s handling of the millions of illegal immigrants who’ve entered our nation is steeped in secrecy. Americans deserve every ounce of transparency to understand the costs & dangers involved with Biden’s unlawful catch-and-release practices.

“In you, Lord, I have taken refuge; let me never be put to shame; deliver me in your righteousness. Turn your ear to me, come quickly to my rescue; be my rock of refuge, a strong fortress to save me.” Psalm 31:1-2

November is #WarriorCareMonth-- a time to honor the bravery, fortitude & sacrifices of wounded, ill & injured service members. Recovery & reintegration to civilian life is a challenge deserving of the utmost support from their fellow Americans. They are an inspiration to us all.

This week, leading up to #VeteransDay, I had the joy of sitting down with Gary Hagen, a Vietnam Dustoff Crew Chief. The Dustoff Crew transported the wounded safely to aid stations & hospitals, & no doubt saved many, many lives. His story is awe-inspiring. Thanks for coming by!

The sacrifices of our veterans & of their families go beyond what many of us can even imagine. As Americans, we have a responsibility to remember, honor, & support them however we can. So grateful for our service men & women. God Bless them & God Bless America  #VeteransDay

Sometimes, it is the smallest gesture that makes the biggest impact, especially for those veterans struggling with the aftermath of their service. On this #WarriorCallDay, pick up the phone & connect with a veteran -- it may make all the difference. https://warriorcall.org
